<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F3EFEB048F757CCFE75FECF" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="007606418F3EFEB048F757CCFE75FECF" blockId="368.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F3EFEB048F757CCFE9EFF08" bold="true" box="[199,315,224,248]" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Remarks.</emphasis>
The female specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18F3EFEB04ABE57F3FCA6FF07" box="[654,771,223,247]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868F3EFEB04B2357F3FCCAFF07" box="[787,879,223,247]" degrees="07" direction="north" minutes="57" orientation="latitude" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" precision="925" value="7.95">07°57'N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868F3EFEB04B4C57F3FC72FF07" box="[892,983,223,247]" degrees="80" direction="east" minutes="46" orientation="longitude" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" precision="925" value="80.76667">80°46'E</geoCoordinate>
, has 5-segmented maxillary palps; the palpal formula 5/2 is typical of the group 10 (former genus 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F3EFEB04B0D5628FBF4FEEC" authority="Richards" authorityName="Richards" authorityYear="1939" box="[829,1105,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Donisthorpina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F3EFEB04B0D5628FC45FEEC" box="[829,992,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">Donisthorpina</emphasis>
Richards
</taxonomicName>
); for this reason, 
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28F3EFEB04D275628FA24FEEC" authorityName="Xu &amp; Olmi &amp; He" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ponomarenko" baseAuthorityYear="1981" box="[1303,1409,260,284]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Gonatopus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="368" pageNumber="369" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lankae">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F3EFEB04D275628FA24FEEC" box="[1303,1409,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="368" pageNumber="369">G. lankae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also included into group 10.
</paragraph>
